ðŸ”¢ LASER CLASSIFICATION

What is Class IIIb (and other laser classes)?

Lasers are classified by how dangerous they are, based on power output:

Class	Power	Effect

Class I	<0.4 Î¼W	Eye-safe under all conditions
Class II	<1 mW	Safe for accidental exposure
Class IIIa	1â€“5 mW	Can damage eyes with direct exposure
âœ… Class IIIb	5â€“500 mW	Dangerous to eyes, may burn skin
âš ï¸ Class IV	>500 mW	Very dangerous, can burn, start fires, damage sensors


So Class IIIb lasers are often used in anti-sensor or experimental toolsâ€”they're strong but not yet "weapons-grade."


