ðŸŒˆ INFRARED & VISIBLE LIGHT: WAVELENGTH

What is 850â€“940 nm IR?

"nm" stands for nanometer, which is how we measure the wavelength of light.

850â€“940 nm is in the near-infrared (IR) spectrumâ€”invisible to the human eye, but visible to IR sensors.


Wavelength	Light Type	Used In

400â€“700 nm	Visible (RGB)	Human vision, RGB cameras
850â€“940 nm	Near-IR	Depth cameras, night vision, IR LEDs
1064 nm	Deeper IR (Nd:YAG)	Military rangefinders, laser jammers



